INSERT INTO recipes2 (id, aou_id, name, recipe) VALUES (44,0,'Making Implants','<font color=#FF0000> A bit of Theory.. </font><font color=#009B00>\n    Implants are support structures for holding clusters. It is the cluster that enhances a skill.\nEach Basic Implant has 3 empty slots that can be loaded with clusters of the proper type. There are three types of Clusters : Shining/Bright/Faded. Shining Clusters are the most powerful ones, Bright ones come second and Faded ones are the weakest, in these proportions :\n        </font><font color=#FFFF00> Shining = Bright + Faded </font><font color=#009B00> (to equal QL).\n        </font><font color=#FFFF00> Bright = 60% of Shining </font><font color=#009B00> (to equal QL).\n        </font><font color=#FFFF00> Faded = 40% of Shining </font><font color=#009B00> (to equal QL).\n\nEach Cluster can be fitted in only one slot and on only one specific Basic implant.\n    For example : the Cluster <img src=''rdb://12712''> <a href=''chatcmd:///tell <myname> show me item 102639''>Eye Implant: Pistol, Faded</a> can only be fitted in the Faded slot of a &quot;Eye&quot; implant (<img src=''rdb://12706''> <a href=''chatcmd:///tell <myname> show me item 101102''>A Basic Eye Implant</a>).\n\n</font><font color=#FF0000> Now practical class... </font><font color=#009B00>\n    To combine a Cluster with an Implant (Basic or not, assuming that the targeted slot is free) you just have to find someone with enough Nano-Programming skill. Simply, you pick up the cluster and Shift+Right click on the Implant.\n</font><font color=#FF0000> Recipe</font><font color=#FFFF00>\n | NP, TR, BA* | Cluster + Basic Implant = Upgraded Implant</font><font color=#009B00>\n* Base Ability: QL*2+4 so a ql10 cluster requires 24 in the base ability.\nTR - for treatment requirements check out <a href=''chatcmd:///start http://www.dd.org/~tale/ao/premade-implants.html''>Premade Implants</a>\n\n</font><font color=#FF0000> Things to know : </font><font color=#009B00>\n    - You can combine a Cluster of an higher QL than the Implant, but the Cluster cannot be too low otherwise you won`t be able to combine them. (tolerance : 18% for a Faded, 16% for a Bright and 14% for a Shining).\n    - Depending on Implant QL and Nanoprograming skill,combining any Cluster with an Implant may result in a slightly higher Implant <a href=''chatcmd:///start http://barvaz.net/corky/viewtopic.php?t=290''>Details</a>\nQL 1-49: No Increase\nQL 50-99: 1 Ql per cluster\nQL100-149 2 Qls per cluster\nQL150-199: 3 QLs per cluster\nQL200-249: 4 QLs per cluster\nQL250-299: 5 QLs per cluster \n    - The QL of the Clusters combined with an Implant of a given QL are lowered or upped to this QL.\n    - <a href=''chatcmd:///start http://www.timezulu.com.au/NanoNanny/''>Nanonanny</a> or\n<a href=''chatcmd:///start http://www.kewlpack.com/iMatrix.shtm''>iMatrix</a> are useful to help you design your Implants.\n    - All the Implants require some skill in Treatement, as well as a Secondary Skill (a main attribute) depending on the all clusters fitted in the Implant.  According to this, it may be helpful to put in a not so useful Cluster, just to make this Secondary Skill change to one where you have higher Attribute. Thus allowing you put higher QL of Implant.\n    - Another way to solve this problem is using &quot;Implant Stepping&quot;. This tactic has been modified some patches ago, now you must have your Implant Slot in the Wear panel already empty before putting a new Implant. This still allows you to have a intermediary implant in one Slot upping a main Attribute as you put your final Implant in another Slot (ie : you are two points short in Psy to put your QL60 Head implant, so you use a Chest Implant QL10, with a Bright Psychic Cluster on, which give you +5 Psy). This process still requires you to plan your Implant Scheme a bit more...\n    - Implants with clusters in them can be `cleaned` by anyone with enough skill. (Fixers are very good at this)\n    - Removing the clusters destroys them leaving you with a Basic Implant. (Done with the help of a <a href=''chatcmd:///tell <myname> show me 51''>Implant Disassembly Clinic</a>)');
INSERT INTO recipes2 (id, aou_id, name, recipe) VALUES (45,0,'Building Nanoprograms','<font color=#FF0000> A bit more info... </font><font color=#009B00>\n    Thanks to Aephora for this recipe :). Everything will be done by using :<img src=''rdb://83413''> <a href=''chatcmd:///tell <myname> show me item 147348''>Instruction Disc (A Maker`s Touch)</a> as example.\n    To build a Nanoprogram, you first need to make a Programmed Photon Particle Emitter. The construction of this item requires different ingredients depending on the Instruction Disc. In fact, to make it you need a Symbol Library. To know which one you need, just read the description of the Instruction Disc. In our case, it`ll be a <img src=''rdb://72779''> <a href=''chatcmd:///tell <myname> show me item 144796''>Symbol Library - Medical</a>. As for the Crystal Reflection Pattern (Medical one in this case).\n    \n</font><font color=#FF0000> Ingredients </font><font color=#009B00>\n    - <img src=''rdb://83413''> <a href=''chatcmd:///tell <myname> show me item 147348''>Instruction Disc (A Maker`s Touch)</a>\n    - <img src=''rdb://72779''> <a href=''chatcmd:///tell <myname> show me item 144796''>Symbol Library - Medical</a>\n    - <img src=''rdb://83869''> <a href=''chatcmd:///tell <myname> show me item 144788''>Photon Particle Emitter</a>\n    - <img src=''rdb://72772''> <a href=''chatcmd:///tell <myname> show me item 150274''>Carbonrich Rock</a>\n    - <img src=''rdb://149947''> <a href=''chatcmd:///tell <myname> show me item 150281''>Jensen Personal Ore Extractor</a>\n    - <img src=''rdb://72783''> <a href=''chatcmd:///tell <myname> show me item 144785''>Isotope Separator</a>\n    - <img src=''rdb://99235''> <a href=''chatcmd:///tell <myname> show me item 144784''>Neutron Displacer</a>\n    - <img src=''rdb://72776''> <a href=''chatcmd:///tell <myname> show me item 144778''>Crystal Reflection Pattern - Medical</a>\n	\n</font><font color=#FF0000> Recipe </font><font color=#FFFF00>\n    - | NP,CL | <img 