INSERT INTO recipes2 (id, aou_id, name, recipe) VALUES (71,0,'Instructions for the good old recipes of Mother Bea','<font color=#FF0000> Ingredients </font><font color=#009B00>\n    Before each recipe, a list of ingredients is given. To know where you can find these, just click on the link on the bottom of the recipe`s window.\n    \n</font><font color=#FF0000> Recipes </font><font color=#009B00>\n    Everywhere in this Book, you`ll find the Recipes explained under this form :\n    \n    | SKILL | </font><font color=#FFFF00> [Item 1] + [Item 2] = [Item 3] </font><font color=#009B00>\n    Here this recipe means : Pick Item 1 and Shift+Right Click on Item 2 to get Item 3. Reminder that in this recipe, Item 1 and Item 2 are lost during the process. This manipulation requires some skill in &quot;SKILL&quot;.\n    \n    Or\n    \n    | SKILL | </font><font color=#FFFF00> [Item 1]</font><font color=#FF0000> * </font><font color=#FFFF00>  + [Item 2] = [Item 3] </font><font color=#009B00>\n    Now this recipe means : Pick Item 1 and Shift+Right Click on Item 2 to get Item 3. Same as before but the Item 1 (the tool, in fact) is not lost during the process. As before, this manipulation requires some skill in &quot;SKILL&quot;.\n    \n</font><font color=#FF0000> Shortcuts of Skills </font><font color=#009B00>\n    - CL : Computer Literacy\n    - NP : Nano Programming\n    - ME : Mech Engi*\n    - EE : Elec Engi*\n    - QT : Quantum FT*\n    - WS : Weapon Smt*\n    - PT : Pharma Tech*\n    - CH : Chemistry\n    - BE : Break and Entry\n    - PS : Psychology\n\n    The Skills noted with * can be buffed for 125pts by the Traders.');
